name: potato starch production | potato starch | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/8484/documentation

The potatoes used as input refer to IP production. In the reference the inventory is based on, by-products evolving during starch production were allocated on an economic basis. The inventory refers to potato starch with a water content of 20% by weight.;[This dataset was already contained in the ecoinvent database version 2. It was not individually updated during the transfer to ecoinvent version 3. Life Cycle Impact Assessment results may still have changed, as they are affected by changes in the supply chain, i.e. in other datasets. This dataset was generated following the ecoinvent quality guidelines for version 2. It may have been subject to central changes described in the ecoinvent version 3 change report (http://www.ecoinvent.org/database/ecoinvent-version-3/reports-of-changes/), and the results of the central updates were reviewed extensively. The changes added e.g. consistent water flows and other information throughout the database. The documentation of this dataset can be found in the ecoinvent reports of version 2, which are still available via the ecoinvent website. The change report linked above covers all central changes that were made during the conversion process.]



The production steps required to obtain potato starch from potato tubers were taken into account, including washing of the potatoes, chopping, separation of the potato fruit water, washing, refinering and finally drying of the starch. Processing of process water was included. Infrastructure use is consideration.
category: C:Manufacturing/10:Manufacture of food products/106:Manufacture of grain mill products, starches and starch products/1062:Manufacture of starches and starch products

processDocumentation.timeDescription: Year when the data for this inventory was delivered.
processDocumentation.geographyDescription: Values refer to the situation in Germany.
processDocumentation.technologyDescription: Refers to typical potato starch production in Germany.
processDocumentation.dataTreatmentDescription: Potato production in Germany approximated by Swiss data. This dataset has been copied from an original dataset covering the geography DE. The uncertainty has been adjusted accordingly.
processDocumentation.samplingDescription: Data based on a detailed literature study.
